    "created_at": "2014-09-14T22:55:48Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-09-14T22:55:48Z",
    "body": "Constant checking -- which detects this recursion -- occurs after type checking in the phase order, but type checking needs to evaluate the constant expression in order to find the length of the array type.  It looks like strategically inserting a call to `check_const::check_item_recursion` in the appropriate place would fix this at the cost of potentially performing the check many times.\n",
